other_tests.findings: The appendix appears dilated up to 14 mm with wall thickening and mild surrounding inflammatory changes suggestive of acute uncomplicated appendicitis. There is no evidence of perforation. Minimal atelectatic changes at lung bases, normal heart size, small hiatal hernia, cholelithiasis without cholecystitis, normal liver, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys, no free fluid or free air, and no lymphadenopathy by CT size criteria.
